The paper deals with the issue of interactions between components in distributed systems, which is a central concern in the field of Distributed Computing (cs.DC). The use of Petri nets as a system model suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The investigation of different notions of distribution and their impact on the validity of synchronous interaction suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). The consideration of semi-structural properties of Petri nets suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of Programming Languages (cs.PL). Finally, the investigation of synchronizations as crucial system properties suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
